<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF829AF828AEFEB0FA4C" blockId="7.[132,776,1492,2030]" box="[132,277,1492,1518]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF829AF8288FFC48FC10" blockId="7.[132,776,1492,2030]" lastBlockId="7.[813,1456,217,945]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
Body size: 
<quantity id="F43430C19E15FF829B7D288FFEE2F9AE" box="[257,327,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
× 
<quantity id="F43430C19E15FF829B1B288FFE63F9AE" box="[359,454,1525,1551]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Body as in 
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829829288FFD03F9AE" box="[597,678,1525,1551]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
. Colour dark brown: antennal peduncle with first and second articles slightly pigmented, third to fifth article and flagellum strongly pigmented; cephalon with irregular unpigmented spots; pereon with longitudinal unpigmented spots on paramedian region, epimera with one unpigmented spot; pleon and telson strongly pigmented; uropods slightly pigmented (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829AF12BAEFF7DF94F" box="[141,216,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface bearing short triangular scale-setae (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829AF22B8EFF45F8AF" box="[142,224,1780,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Cephalon (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829BFC2B8EFE5EF8AF" box="[384,507,1780,1806]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4C, D</figureCitation>
) without lateral lobes, frontal line and supra-antennal slightly bent downwards medially; vertex dorsoventrally flattened with prominent compound eyes on lateral protrusions; eyes with 25 ommatidia arranged in four rows. Pleon (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8298432A09FD2AF82C" box="[575,655,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) narrower than pereon, neopleurae 3-5 well developed and directed backwards. Telson (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829B1D2AC9FE0AF86C" box="[353,431,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) with lateral margins concave, apex rounded. Antennula (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829BC82AA9FDA5F84C" box="[436,512,2003,2029]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) of three articles, distal article bearing six aesthetascs in three sets plus apical pair. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299DF2D83FC5CFEB2" box="[931,1017,249,275]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1987,2005]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,259,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[133,1456,214,1877]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, habitus, dorsal view; B, dorsal scale-seta; C, cephalon, dorsal view; D, cephalon, frontal view; E, pleonite 5 and telson; F, antennula; G, antenna. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) when extended posteriorly reaching anterior margin of pereonite 3; flagellum of three articles subequal in length, apical organ very long. Mandibles with molar penicil composed of 5 to 6 branches, left mandible (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF82991C2C03FC14FE32" box="[864,945,376,403]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) with 2+1 penicils, right mandible (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829F2A2C03FA03FE32" box="[1366,1446,376,403]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) with 1+1 penicils. Maxillula (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829EFF2CE2FB70FE12" box="[1155,1237,408,435]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) inner endite with distal margin rounded bearing two stout hairy penicils; outer endite of 4+6 teeth, two of them with cleft apex. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299E82C82FC4DFDB2" box="[916,1000,504,531]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) outer lobe twice as wide as inner lobe, distal margin rounded and covered with thin setae, two thick setae on inner portion; inner lobe rounded bearing thick setae. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829E402F22FB2CFDD2" box="[1084,1161,600,627]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) basis rectangular bearing sparse setae; palp with two setae on proximal article; endite sub-rectangular, median seta surpassing distal margin, strong seta on distal outer portion, ventral surface setose. Uropod (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299E92FADFC7AFD53" box="[917,991,727,754]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,1391,1409]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[132,1455,216,1342]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz,López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp.,male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40).A, left mandible;B, right mandible;C, maxillula inner endite (right), outer endite (left); D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, uropod." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726221" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726221/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
) protopod and exopod grooved on lateral margin, exopod longer than endopod, endopod inserted proximally. Pereopods 1-7 long and slender, carpus 1 with antennal grooming brush transverse; dactylus of two claws, inner claw not surpassing outer claw, ungual seta long, dactylar seta apically plumose. Pleopod exopods without respiratory areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF8299512EACFCC7FC51" blockId="7.[813,1456,982,1583]" box="[813,866,982,1008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="01B841369E15FF8299512EACFCC7FC51" box="[813,866,982,1008]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF8299512E8CFC7DF98E" blockId="7.[813,1456,982,1583]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
Pereopod 1 (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299C92E8CFBA7FBB1" box="[949,1026,1014,1040]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
) with merus, carpus and propodus, and pereopod 2 merus and carpus bearing dense field of setae. Pereopod 7 (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299C6294CFBACFBF1" box="[954,1033,1078,1104]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
) ischium with rounded depression on rostral surface, sternal margin bearing brush of thin setae on central part. Genital papilla (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829EF5290CFB7DFB31" box="[1161,1240,1142,1168]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) truncated apically, triangular ventral shield and two apical orifices. Pleopod 1 (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF82994A29CCFC2CFB71" box="[822,905,1206,1232]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
) exopod cordiform, inner margin almost straight, outer margin without lateral incision, distal margin rounded, lateral process short; endopod stout, almost twice as long as exopod, distal portion straight bearing row of small setae on medial margin and subapical lobe on outer margin. Pleopod 2 (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299FE282FFC77FACE" box="[898,978,1365,1391]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
) exopod triangular, outer margin concave bearing several setae; endopod stout, slightly longer than exopod. Pleopods 3 and 4 as in 
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF829EFB28EFFA85FA0E" box="[1159,1312,1429,1455]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6F and G</figureCitation>
, respectively. Pleopod 5 (
<figureCitation id="ABF781A19E15FF8299D228CFFBA4FA6E" box="[942,1025,1461,1487]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[132,143,1986,2004]" captionTargetBox="[139,1450,243,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[132,1455,214,1927]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Ischioscia perijaensis Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho n. sp., male paratype (CUDC-CRU 40): A, pereopod 1; B, pereopod 7; C, genital papilla; D, pleopod 1, exopod (right), endopod (left); E, pleopod 2; F, pleopod 3; G, pleopod 4; H, pleopod 5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3726223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3726223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
) exopod rhomboid slightly wider than long, transverse rows of scales, outer margin sinuous bearing four setae, inner and outer margins densely covered with thin setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7BD6CEAF9E15FF8299512B2EFB9CF84C" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF8299512B2EFC34F9CD" blockId="7.[813,1456,1620,2029]" box="[813,913,1620,1646]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33739D249E15FF8299512B0EFB9CF84C" blockId="7.[813,1456,1620,2029]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicName id="F4CCE6A79E15FF8299512B0EFA8EF92F" authority="Carpio-Diaz, Lopez-Orozco" authorityName="Carpio-Diaz, Lopez-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[813,1323,1652,1678]" class="Malacostraca" family="Philosciidae" genus="Ischioscia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perijaensis">
<emphasis id="01B841369E15FF8299512B0EFC5CF92F" box="[813,1017,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Ischioscia perijaensis</emphasis>
Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco
</taxonomicName>
&amp; Campos- Filho n. sp. is readily distinguishable from their congeners in having the male pereopod 1 carpus not enlarged, the male pereopod 7 ischium with a rounded depression on rostral surface, and the male pleopod 1 exopod cordiform with lateral process short and outer margin lacking the lateral incision. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="F4CCE6A79E15FF829EFC2A4EFB36F8CC" authority="Carpio-Diaz, Lopez-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho" authorityName="Carpio-Diaz, Lopez-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho" authorityYear="2020" class="Malacostraca" family="Philosciidae" genus="Ischioscia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perijaensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="01B841369E15FF829EFC2A4EFAABF8EC" box="[1152,1294,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">I. perijaensis</emphasis>
Carpio-Díaz, López-Orozco &amp; Campos-Filho
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1A8BFC4D9E15FF829EE72A2EFB7DF8CF" box="[1179,1240,1876,1902]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F4CCE6A79E15FF829F172A2EFAF0F82C" authority="Lopez-Orozco, Carpio-Diaz &amp; Campos-Filho" authorityName="Lopez-Orozco, Carpio-Diaz &amp; Campos-Filho" authorityYear="2020" class="Malacostraca" family="Philosciidae" genus="Ischioscia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrerai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="01B841369E15FF829F172A2EFCF8F82C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">I. herrerai</emphasis>
López-Orozco, Carpio-Díaz &amp; Campos-Filho
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1A8BFC4D9E15FF829F262A0EFA31F82F" box="[1370,1428,1908,1934]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the male pereopod 1 carpus not enlarged, the male pereopod 7 ischium without lobe and in the shape of the male pleopod 1 exopod.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
